<title>USA: TABLE-Western Micro Q2 net income lower.</title>
<headline>TABLE-Western Micro Q2 net income lower.</headline>
<dateline>CAMPBELL, Calif. 1997-07-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Western Micro Technology Inc</p>
<p>		  (In thousands, except per share amounts)</p>
<p>				  For the Three Months Ended June 30,</p>
<p>						   1997		 1996</p>
<p> Net Sales				 $ 39,886	   $ 32,365</p>
<p> Cost of goods sold			33,293	     28,459</p>
<p> Gross profit				 6,593		3,906</p>
<p> Net income				     407		  486</p>
<p> Net income per common share	     0.08		 0.11</p>
<p> Number of shares used		    5,240		4,529</p>
<p>					     Six Months Ended June 30,</p>
<p>						   1997		  1996</p>
<p> Net Sales				 $ 75,836	    $ 59,981</p>
<p> Cost of goods sold			63,274		52,495</p>
<p> Gross profit				12,562		 7,486</p>
<p> Net income				     950		   857</p>
<p> Net income per common share	     0.19		  0.19</p>
<p>Number of shares used</p>
<p>   in per share calculation	     5,106		 4,443</p>
<p>NOET: Co said Q2 profits did not meet expectations as previously announced on July 16, 1997. Western Micro attributes the shortfall to unusual events that occurred during the quarter including: consolidation of operations in Southern California, the move of main warehouse and integration operations to a larger building, senior management resource dilution due to significant acquisition-related activities and delay in completing an anticipated private equity financing.</p>
<p>-- New York Newsdesk 212 859-1610</p>
